MRI Data¶

I completed this project for Dalhousie's NESC 3505: Neural Data Science course. The course and the instructions were written and taught by Dr. Aaron Newman. Here, I worked with Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) datasets.

View Multiple Slices¶

In [9]:
fig1 = plt.figure(figsize=[8, 12])
subplot_counter = 1

for ii in range(0, 160, 10):
    fig1.add_subplot(4, 4, subplot_counter)
    plt.imshow(vol[ii], cmap='gray')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.tight_layout()
    subplot_counter +=1

plt.show()

brain_mask = np.where(brain_img >125, 1, 0)
plt.imshow(brain_mask, cmap='gray')
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

In [14]:
# I can now use the brain mask to exclude data from voxels that are outside of the mask and plot a histogram of only voxels inside the brain mask. 
voxels_inside = np.where(brain_mask == 1, brain_img, np.nan)
hist = ndi.histogram(voxels_inside, min=0, max=300, bins=300)
plt.plot(hist)
plt.show()
